    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="diplomatic" ana="b1">
                <p>
               <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/>
               <g type="cross"/>
               <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/>
               <lb/> Α<g type="cross"/>Ω<lb/>
                    <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/>ΑΡϹΙΜΑ<gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
               <lb/>
                    <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/>ΙΟϹ ΜΑΞΙ<lb/> ΜΟΥ ΕΤΩΝ<lb/>
                    <hi rend="supraline">
                  <supplied reason="lost">Κ</supplied>Α</hi> ΕΤΟΥϹ<lb/> ΑΛΥ <g type="cross"/>
            </p>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p><supplied reason="lost">ΙϹ</supplied>
               <g type="cross"/>
               <supplied reason="lost">ΧϹ</supplied>
               <lb/>Α<g type="cross"/>Ω<lb/>
               <supplied reason="lost">Β</supplied>αρσίμα<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied>
               <lb/>
               <supplied reason="lost">υ</supplied>ἱὸς Μαξί<lb break="no"/>μου ἐτῶν<lb/>
               <num value="21">
                  <supplied reason="lost">κ</supplied>α</num> ἐτούς<lb/>
               <num value="431">αλυ</num>
                    <g type="cross"/></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Alpha-omega. Barsimas son of Maximus; aged 21 years, in the year 431.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The missing segment above the arms of the cross could have contained the letters
                    ΙϹ ΧϹ, Ἰ(ησοῦ)ς Χ(ριστό)ς, which complete the formula: "Jesus Christ, the alpha
                    and the omega, the beginning and the end" (Revelation 22:13). The year of
                    Barsimas death, 431, was probably determined according to the ear of Panias
                    (Caesarea-Philippi), the provincial capital whose rule extended over the north
                    part of the Golan Heights: it would be equivalent to 429/430 CE.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
